"display: none;" transform="matrix(1,0,0,1,16,16)" opacity="1" wfd-invisible="true"><g opacity="1" transform="matrix(1,0,0,1,0,0)"><path stroke="url(#__lottie_element_500)" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="miter" fill-opacity="0" stroke-miterlimit="4" stroke-opacity="1" stroke-width="2" d=" M-4.500999927520752,-14.312000274658203 C-3.0799999237060547,-14.758999824523926 -1.5679999589920044,-15 0,-15 C0,-15 0,-15 0,-15 C1.6670000553131104,-15 3.2709999084472656,-14.72700023651123 4.769999980926514,-14.223999977111816"></path></g></g><g style="display: none;" wfd-invisible="true"><g><path stroke="url(#__lottie_element_496)" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="miter" fill-opacity="0" stroke-miterlimit="4"></path></g></g><g style="display: none;" wfd-invisible="true"><g><path stroke="url(#__lottie_element_492)" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="miter" fill-opacity="0" stroke-miterlimit="4"></path></g></g><g style="display: none;" wfd-invisible="true"><g><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="miter" fill-opacity="0" stroke-miterlimit="4"></path></g></g><g style="display: none;" wfd-invisible="true"><g><path stroke="url(#__lottie_element_485)" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="miter" fill-opacity="0" stroke-miterlimit="4"></path></g></g></g></svg></div></div></bard-avatar><!----><!----></div><!----><div _ngcontent-ng-c1883881203="" class="response-container-content ng-tns-c1883881203-26"><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><div _ngcontent-ng-c3748022998="" class="response-content ng-tns-c1883881203-26"><!----><div _ngcontent-ng-c3748022998="" class="thoughts-container ng-star-inserted"><!----></div><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><h2 _ngcontent-ng-c3748022998="" class="cdk-visually-hidden ng-star-inserted">Gemini a dit</h2><!----><!----><structured-content-container _ngcontent-ng-c3748022998="" class="model-response-text processing-state-visible ng-star-inserted" _nghost-ng-c4085131935="" style="height: auto;"><div _ngcontent-ng-c4085131935="" class="container"><message-content _ngcontent-ng-c4085131935="" _nghost-ng-c3807329646="" id="message-content-id-r_26d6f45e0d1b17e8" class="ng-star-inserted"><div _ngcontent-ng-c3807329646="" inline-copy-host="" class="markdown markdown-main-panel stronger enable-updated-hr-color" style="--animation-duration: 400ms; --fade-animation-function: linear;" id="model-response-message-contentr_26d6f45e0d1b17e8" aria-live="off" aria-busy="false" dir="ltr"><p data-path-to-node="0">In 2026, the answer is <b data-path-to-node="0" data-index-in-node="23">yes</b>, but with a twist. <b data-path-to-node="0" data-index-in-node="46">Firebase Studio</b> (which evolved from Project IDX) can absolutely create this, but it isn’t a "drag-and-drop" website builder. Instead, it is an <b data-path-to-node="0" data-index-in-node="189">Agentic Development Environment</b>.</p><p data-path-to-node="1">This means you don't need to "code" in the traditional sense, but you do need to <b data-path-to-node="1" data-index-in-node="81">manage the AI agent</b> while it builds the extension for you.</p><hr data-path-to-node="2"><h2 data-path-to-node="3">🛠️ How to use Firebase Studio (No-Code Method)</h2><h3 data-path-to-node="4">1. Launch the Workspace</h3><p data-path-to-node="5">Go to <response-element class="" ng-version="0.0.0-PLACEHOLDER"><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><link-block _nghost-ng-c1796846746="" class="ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----><a _ngcontent-ng-c1796846746="" target="_blank" rel="noopener" externallink="" _nghost-ng-c412475248="" jslog="197247;track:generic_click,impression,attention;BardVeMetadataKey:[[&quot;r_26d6f45e0d1b17e8&quot;,&quot;c_900130c3d9008f9e&quot;,null,&quot;rc_1688b10e6e3bf871&quot;,null,null,&quot;en&quot;,null,1,null,null,1,0]]" href="https://studio.firebase.google.com/" class="ng-star-inserted" data-hveid="0" decode-data-ved="1" data-ved="0CAAQ_4QMahcKEwihq_2QlpqTAxUAAAAAHQAAAAAQUQ">studio.firebase.google.com</a><!----></link-block><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></response-element>. Choose the <b data-path-to-node="5" data-index-in-node="45">"App Prototyping"</b> agent or start a blank <b data-path-to-node="5" data-index-in-node="86">Web</b> workspace.</p><h3 data-path-to-node="6">2. Prompt the AI Agent</h3><p data-path-to-node="7">In the chat panel, you don't write code; you provide a "spec." Use this exact prompt to ensure it works in 2026:</p><blockquote data-path-to-node="8"><p data-path-to-node="8,0">"Act as a Chrome Extension Developer. Build a Manifest V3 extension.
<b data-path-to-node="8,0" data-index-in-node="69">Feature:</b> When I right-click an image, show a menu item 'Analyze Image Integrity'.
<b data-path-to-node="8,0" data-index-in-node="151">Action:</b> On click, get the image source URL and open a new tab to <code data-path-to-node="8,0" data-index-in-node="216">https://29a.ch/photo-forensics/#ela</code> with that image loaded.
<b data-path-to-node="8,0" data-index-in-node="276">Structure:</b> I need the manifest.json, background.js, and an icon placeholder."</p></blockquote><h3 data-path-to-node="9">3. Let the Agent "Cook"</h3><p data-path-to-node="10">Firebase Studio’s Gemini agent will generate the files in the left-hand sidebar.</p><ul data-path-to-node="11"><li><p data-path-to-node="11,0,0">It will create the <code data-path-to-node="11,0,0" data-index-in-node="19">manifest.json</code> (the ID card of your extension).</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node="11,1,0">It will create the <code data-path-to-node="11,1,0" data-index-in-node="19">background.js</code> (the logic that handles the right-click).</p></li></ul><h3 data-path-to-node="12">4. The "One-Click" Testing</h3><p data-path-to-node="13">Firebase Studio has a <b data-path-to-node="13" data-index-in-node="22">built-in browser preview</b>, but for a Chrome Extension, you need to test it in your actual browser.</p><ol start="1" data-path-to-node="14"><li><p data-path-to-node="14,0,0">Click the <b data-path-to-node="14,0,0" data-index-in-node="10">"Export"</b> or <b data-path-to-node="14,0,0" data-index-in-node="22">"Download"</b> button in Firebase Studio to get your project folder.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node="14,1,0">Go to <code data-path-to-node="14,1,0" data-index-in-node="6">chrome://extensions</code> in your browser.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node="14,2,0">Turn on <b data-path-to-node="14,2,0" data-index-in-node="8">Developer Mode</b>.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node="14,3,0">Click <b data-path-to-node="14,3,0" data-index-in-node="6">Load Unpacked</b> and select the folder Firebase Studio gave you.</p></li></ol><hr data-path-to-node="15"><h2 data-path-to-node="16">🤖 Why Firebase Studio is better than other builders</h2><ul data-path-to-node="17"><li><p data-path-to-node="17,0,0"><b data-path-to-node="17,0,0" data-index-in-node="0">Agentic Debugging:</b> If the extension doesn't work, you just type: <i data-path-to-node="17,0,0" data-index-in-node="65">"The right-click menu isn't showing up, please fix it,"</i> and the AI will rewrite the files automatically.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node="17,1,0"><b data-path-to-node="17,1,0" data-index-in-node="0">Direct Firebase Integration:</b> If you later want to save "Scanned Reports" to a database, you can just tell the agent: <i data-path-to-node="17,1,0" data-index-in-node="117">"Add a Firestore database to save every image URL I scan,"</i> and it will set up the backend for you.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node="17,2,0"><b data-path-to-node="17,2,0" data-index-in-node="0">Zero Setup:</b> You don't need to install Node.js or any software on your computer. It all happens in the Google Cloud.</p></li></ul><hr data-path-to-node="18"><h2 data-path-to-node="19">⚠️ The "Free" Catch</h2><p data-path-to-node="20">While Firebase Studio is free to use (with a generous preview tier in 2026), creating a professional-grade integrity tool like <b data-path-to-node="20" data-index-in-node="127">Proofig</b> requires a "Brain."</p><p data-path-to-node="21">Your extension will be a "Shortcut" to forensic sites. If you want the extension to do the AI analysis <i data-path-to-node="21" data-index-in-node="103">itself</i> without leaving the page, you would eventually need to connect it to an API (like Google Vision or a specialized Forensic API), which might have costs after the first 1,000 scans.</p><p data-path-to-node="22"><b data-path-to-node="22" data-index-in-node="0">Would you like me to write out the specific "Manifest V3" text for you to copy-paste into Firebase Studio right now?</b></p></div></message-content><!----></div></structured-content-container><!----><!----><div _ngcontent-ng-c3748022998="" class="response-footer gap complete"><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><div _ngcontent-ng-c3748022998="" role="status" class="stopped-draft-message gds-body-l gds-italic ng-star-inserted" hidden="" wfd-invisible="true">Vous avez interrompu cette réponse</div><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></div></div><!----><sensitive-memories-banner _ngcontent-ng-c3748022998="" _nghost-ng-c3363139195="" class="ng-star-inserted" style=""><!----></sensitive-memories-banner><!----><!----><!----></div></div><div _ngcontent-ng-c1883881203="" class="response-container-footer ng-tns-c1883881203-26 ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----><message-actions _ngcontent-ng-c3748022998="" footer="" _nghost-ng-c3060034751="" class="ng-tns-c3060034751-28 ng-star-inserted hide-action-bar" style=""><div _ngcontent-ng-c3060034751="" class="actions-container-v2 ng-tns-c3060034751-28"><div _ngcontent-ng-c3060034751="" class="buttons-container-v2 ng-tns-c3060034751-28 ng-star-inserted"><!----><thumb-up-button _ngcontent-ng-c3060034751="" _nghost-ng-c885881154="" class="ng-tns-c3060034751-28 ng-star-inserted"><button _ngcontent-ng-c885881154="" mat-icon-button="" mattooltip="Bonne réponse" aria-label="Bonne réponse" class="mdc-icon-button mat-mdc-icon-button mat-mdc-button-base mat-mdc-tooltip-trigger icon-button mat-unthemed" mat-ripple-loader-uninitialized="" mat-ripple-loader-class-name="mat-mdc-button-ripple" mat-ripple-loader-centered="" aria-pressed="false" jslog="173913;track:generic_click,impression;BardVeMetadataKey:[[&quot;r_26d6f45e0d1b17e8&quot;,&quot;c_900130c3d9008f9e&quot;,null,&quot;rc_1688b10e6e3bf871&quot;,null,null,&quot;en&quot;,null,1,null,null,1,0]];mutable:true"><span class="mat-mdc-button-persistent-ripple mdc-icon-button__ripple"></span><mat-icon _ngcontent-ng-c885881154="" role="img" fonticon="thumb_up" class="mat-icon notranslate gds-icon-m google-symbols mat-ligature-font mat-icon-no-color ng-star-inserted" aria-hidden="true" data-mat-icon-type="font" data-mat-icon-name="thumb_up"></mat-icon><!----><div _ngcontent-ng-c885881154="" lottie-animation="" class="thumb-animation" hidden="" wfd-invisible="true"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/199